{
  "name": "Approval Step 2: Execute Approval Tests",
  "version": "7.0.0",
  "description": "Execute approval workflows using testing framework with real-time progress reporting for ENHANCEMENTS (E in RICE)",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Execute Step 2: Run Approval Tests with Real-Time Progress\n\n**CONTEXT:** Execute approval test scenarios using the automated testing framework. The framework will show real-time progress as it executes each step.\n\n**WORKFLOW TYPE:** Approval workflows (Enhancements - E in RICE) with Extension IDs starting with EXT_\n\n**STEP 1: USER SELECTION (Interactive)**\n1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects client\n2. List test scenario JSON files in Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/ → User selects file\n   - Look for files matching pattern: *_auto_approval_test.json\n   - Show file size and modification date\n   - Extension IDs start with EXT_ (not INT_)\n   - Example: EXT_FIN_004_auto_approval_test.json\n\n**STEP 2: PROMPT FOR CREDENTIALS**\n3. Ask user for FSM credentials:\n   - FSM Portal URL (e.g., https://acuity-tst.inforcloudsuite.com)\n   - FSM Username (e.g., ACUITY_TST#username)\n   - FSM Password\n\n**STEP 3: EXECUTE TESTS**\n4. Run the test execution script with credentials:\n   ```bash\n   python ReusableTools/run_approval_tests_v2.py --client {ClientName} --scenario {scenario_file_path} --environment {ClientName} --url \"{FSM_URL}\" --username \"{FSM_USERNAME}\" --password \"{FSM_PASSWORD}\"\n   ```\n\n**WHAT TO EXPECT:**\nThe script will show real-time progress:\n- Initialization messages\n- Scenario execution (e.g., \"SCENARIO 1/3: 3.1 - Valid Invoice Approval\")\n- Step-by-step progress (e.g., \"⏳ Step 1.1: Login to FSM\")\n- Pass/fail status for each step (✅ PASSED or ❌ FAILED)\n- Error messages if steps fail\n- Final test results summary\n- TES-070 document path when complete\n\n**BROWSER BEHAVIOR:**\n- Browser will open on your 2nd screen (if available)\n- Browser stays visible so you can watch the automation\n- Browser will close automatically when tests complete\n- If browser appears stuck, check the console output for details\n\n**EXECUTION TIME:**\n- Typical: 5-10 minutes per scenario\n- Depends on: Number of scenarios, FSM response time, approval workflow complexity\n- Framework shows progress so you know it's working\n\n**STEP 4: MONITOR EXECUTION**\n5. Watch the console output for:\n   - Current scenario being executed\n   - Current step being executed\n   - Pass/fail status\n   - Any error messages\n   - Work unit IDs (captured automatically)\n\n6. Watch the browser for:\n   - Login process\n   - Navigation to Payables/GL/Cash\n   - Form filling\n   - Approval submission\n   - Work unit monitoring\n   - Status verification\n\n**STEP 5: HANDLE ERRORS**\n7. If a step fails:\n   - Framework shows error message immediately\n   - Critical failures (login, navigation) stop scenario execution\n   - Non-critical failures continue to next step\n   - All failures documented in TES-070\n\n8. Common errors and solutions:\n   - Login failed: Check credentials, check FSM URL\n   - Navigation failed: FSM UI may have changed, check selectors\n   - Timeout: FSM may be slow, increase timeout in JSON\n   - Element not found: FSM UI may have changed, update selectors\n\n**STEP 6: REVIEW RESULTS**\n9. When execution completes, framework shows:\n   - Total scenarios executed\n   - Pass/fail count\n   - TES-070 document path\n   - Evidence folder location\n\n10. Framework automatically:\n    - Captures screenshots at key steps\n    - Saves evidence to Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/\n    - Generates TES-070 document at Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Generated_TES070s/\n    - Documents work unit IDs\n    - Records pass/fail status\n\n**STEP 7: VERIFY OUTPUT**\n11. Check that files were created:\n    - TES-070 document: Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Generated_TES070s/TES-070_{timestamp}_{extension_id}.docx\n    - Evidence folder: Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/{scenario_id}/\n    - Screenshots: *.png files in evidence folders\n\n12. Quick validation:\n    ```python\n    from pathlib import Path\n    \n    # Check TES-070\n    tes070_dir = Path('Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Generated_TES070s')\n    recent_docs = sorted(tes070_dir.glob('*.docx'), key=lambda p: p.stat().st_mtime, reverse=True)\n    if recent_docs:\n        print(f'✓ TES-070 created: {recent_docs[0].name}')\n        print(f'  Size: {recent_docs[0].stat().st_size / 1024:.1f} KB')\n    \n    # Check evidence\n    evidence_dir = Path('Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence')\n    if evidence_dir.exists():\n        scenario_folders = list(evidence_dir.glob('*.*'))\n        total_screenshots = sum(len(list(f.glob('*.png'))) for f in scenario_folders)\n        print(f'✓ Evidence: {len(scenario_folders)} scenarios, {total_screenshots} screenshots')\n    ```\n\n**STEP 8: COMPLETION**\n13. Confirm completion:\n    - ✅ Step 2 complete!\n    - 📊 {passed}/{total} scenarios passed\n    - 📄 TES-070 document generated\n    - 📸 Evidence captured\n    - 🚀 Next: Click \"Approval Step 3: Review TES-070 Document\"\n\n**TROUBLESHOOTING:**\n- Script not found: Check you're in workspace root directory\n- Credentials rejected: Verify URL, username, password format\n- Browser doesn't open: Check Playwright installation (python -m playwright install chromium)\n- Script appears stuck: Check console output for current step, check browser for activity\n- No progress shown: Check if script is running (should show real-time updates)\n- TES-070 not generated: Check for errors in console output\n- Screenshots missing: Check evidence folder exists and has write permissions\n\n**IMPORTANT NOTES:**\n- Framework runs in standalone mode (no Kiro/MCP dependency)\n- Uses standard Python Playwright (not MCP tools)\n- Browser displays on 2nd screen for visibility\n- All credentials passed via command-line (not stored)\n- Progress shown in real-time (no more \"stuck\" feeling)\n- TES-070 generated automatically (no manual step needed)\n- Evidence preserved for review in Step 3\n\n**SECURITY:**\n- Credentials passed as command-line arguments (not logged)\n- Credentials not stored in files\n- Browser closes automatically after execution\n- Evidence folder contains no sensitive data\n\nAfter completion, tell the user: 'Step 2 complete. Executed {total} scenarios with {passed} passed and {failed} failed. TES-070 document generated at: {tes070_path}. Evidence saved to: Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/. Run Approval Step 3 to review and finalize the TES-070 document.'"
  },
  "enabled": true,
  "workspaceFolderName": "Automated_Testing",
  "shortName": "approval-step2-v7"
}
